                            <comment id="484653" author="bzzz" created="Tue, 20 Jan 2026 17:12:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I checked few sessions - grant check is done few few times over a whole sanity, then I tried to enable it for every subtest and immediately did hit in 27o - it&apos;s easy to reproduce with just ONLY=27 (but you need to comment one line out in check_grant()). failed 63a could be just a postponed result.&lt;br/&gt;
specifically 27o seem to fail due to OBD_FAIL_OST_ENOSPC - the client is returned ENOSPC before any handling on OST (including grants),&lt;br/&gt;
then brw_interpret() -&amp;gt; osc_extent_finish() -&amp;gt; osc_free_grant() drops cl_dirty_grant, but do not increase cl_avail_grant:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
	cli-&amp;gt;cl_dirty_pages -= nr_pages;
	cli-&amp;gt;cl_lost_grant += lost_grant;
	cli-&amp;gt;cl_dirty_grant -= dirty_grant;
	&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (cli-&amp;gt;cl_avail_grant &amp;lt; grant &amp;amp;&amp;amp; cli-&amp;gt;cl_lost_grant &amp;gt;= grant) {
		/* borrow some grant from truncate to avoid the &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; that
		 * truncate uses up all avail grant */
		cli-&amp;gt;cl_lost_grant -= grant;
		cli-&amp;gt;cl_avail_grant += grant;
	}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;so we change nothing on OST side and just drop dirty on the client side while check_grant() supposes that granted on OST = dirty + available on the client&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
